{"article_id":"rr8ZhnSLaOCfvaYO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"poster= '' http : //v. .com/images/1155968404/201706/2779/1155968404_5456531505001_5456474518001-vs.jpg","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"? pubId=1155968404 ''","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Trump announces U.S. withdrawal from Paris climate deal","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"The news follows weeks of intrigue about the pact","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that nearly 200 nations agreed to in December 2015 .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"President Donald Trump announced Thursday","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that he will pull out of the Paris climate agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"delivering the news in a Rose Garden speech","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"loaded with the `` America First '' rhetoric of his presidential campaign .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Trump said","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"he 'd be willing to reenter an international climate deal","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"if he could secure better terms for the United States","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"- although France , Germany , Italy and the United Nations immediately poured water on the idea","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"of renegotiating the nearly 200-nation Paris accord ,","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"and one European official called it a `` Trumpian ruse . ''","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"The president made it clear Thursday","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"that he ha s no interest","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"in remaining in a deal","depth":14},{"id":18,"text":"he consider s harmful to the U.S. ,","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"regardless of what the rest of the world might think .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"\" I was elected to represent the citizens of Pittsburgh , not Paris , \"","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"he said to applause from the crowd ,","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"which included conservative activists","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"who had pushed for him to exit the agreement .","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"Under terms of the deal , the earliest","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"the U.S. can formally withdraw","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"is just after the next presidential election in November 2020 .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"The United States would join Nicaragua and Syria , the only two countries","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"that declined to participate in the agreement .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Trump ' s words echoed the perspective of nationalists like chief White House strategist Steve Bannon , a major critic of the 2015 deal ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"and seemingly reject s the worldview of the president ' s daughter Ivanka ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"who worried","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"that pulling out would harm U.S. international relations .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"The president ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"who once dismissed the idea of man made climate change as a Chinese-inspired `` hoax , ''","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"even seemed to suggest","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"that the United States is a victim of a global campaign","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"to harm America ' s economy .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"\" The rest of the world applauded","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"when we signed the Paris agreement , ''","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Trump said Thursday .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"`` They went wild ,","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"they were so happy , for the simple reason","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"that it put our country","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"- the United States of America ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"which we all love -","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"at a very , very big economic disadvantage .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"\" A cynic would say","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"the obvious reason","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"for economic competitors and their wish","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"to see us remain in the agreement","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"is so that we continue to suffer the self-inflicted , major economic wound , \"","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"he added .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Criticism and expressions of dismay immediately poured in from the U.S. and around the globe , including from former President Barack Obama ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"who had made achieving a deal in Paris one of the prime diplomatic goals of his administration .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Obama said","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Trump was the one","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"delivering a bad deal for Americans .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Morning Energy newsletter","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"The source for energy and environment news - weekday mornings , in your inbox .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"By signing up","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"`` The nations","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that remain in the Paris Agreement","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"will be the nations","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"that reap the benefits in jobs and industries","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"created .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"I believe","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"the United States of America should be at the front of the pack , ''","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Obama said in a statement .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"`` But even in the absence of American leadership ;","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"even as this Administration joins a small handful of nations","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that reject the future ;","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"I ' m confident","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that our states , cities , and businesses will step up","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"and do even more","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"to lead the way ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"and help protect for future generations the one planet","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"we ' ve got . ''","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Sen. Brian Schatz","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"( D-Hawaii )","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"was much more blunt .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"\" Dear Trump administration :","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Please stop doing insane things , \"","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"he wrote on Twitter .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"\" Signed , Future Generations . \"","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Tesla CEO Elon Musk and Walt Disney CEO Robert Iger reacted","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"by announcing","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"they would quit participating in White House advisory councils","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"because of Trump 's withdrawal .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"\" Climate change is real .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"Leaving Paris is not good for America or the world , ''","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Musk tweeted","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"moments after Trump finished his speech .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"The leaders of other major tech companies ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"including Amazon , Google , Facebook , Microsoft and IBM ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"also expressed their concerns .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said in a statement","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"that Trump ' s move left him \" deeply disappointed , \"","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"adding :","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"\" Canadians know","depth":16},{"id":103,"text":"we need to take decisive and collective action","depth":17},{"id":104,"text":"to tackle the many harsh realities of our changing climate. \"","depth":17},{"id":105,"text":"British Prime Minister Theresa May ,","depth":17},{"id":106,"text":"who faces elections next week ,","depth":17},{"id":107,"text":"similarly \" expressed her disappointment with the decision","depth":16},{"id":108,"text":"and stressed","depth":16},{"id":109,"text":"that the U.K. remained committed to the Paris Agreement , \"","depth":16},{"id":110,"text":"her government said in a statement after her own conversation with Trump on Thursday .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"In France , President Emmanuel Macron shifted to English in a televised address Thursday night","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"to offer an oblique jab at Trump ,","depth":15},{"id":113,"text":"saying ,","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"\" We all share our responsibility :","depth":16},{"id":115,"text":"Make our planet great again . \"","depth":16},{"id":116,"text":"A White House readout of Trump ' s conversations with May , Trudeau , Macron and German Chancellor Angela Merkel said","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"he had thanked them for their \" frank , substantive discussions \" on the issue .","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"Trump also promised","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"that the U.S. will be \" the cleanest and most environmentally friendly country on Earth \" under his presidency .","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"In the U.S. , the governors of California , Washington state and New York announced Thursday","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"that they would form an alliance","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"to take steps","depth":17},{"id":123,"text":"to meet the United States ' climate goals .","depth":17},{"id":124,"text":"The states make up about a fifth of the U.S. population and its gross domestic product .","depth":15},{"id":125,"text":"\" If the President is going to be AWOL in this profoundly important human endeavor ,","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"then California and other states will step up , ''","depth":15},{"id":127,"text":"California Gov . Jerry Brown said in a statement .","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"Pittsburgh 's mayor slammed Trump on Twitter ,","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"despite the affection","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"the president ' s speech had expressed for the Steel City .","depth":16},{"id":131,"text":"\" Pittsburgh stands with the world","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"& will follow Paris Agreement , \"","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"wrote Mayor Bill Peduto ,","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"who had signed on to a letter last year ,","depth":17},{"id":135,"text":"urging Trump to remain in the deal .","depth":17},{"id":136,"text":"But Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"( R-Ky. ) ,","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"a frequent critic of what he called Obama ' s `` war on coal , '' cheered Trump ' s move as a long-awaited deliverance .","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"\" By withdrawing from this unattainable mandate ,","depth":16},{"id":140,"text":"President Trump has reiterated his commitment","depth":17},{"id":141,"text":"to protecting middle - class families across the country and workers throughout coal country from higher energy prices and potential job loss , \"","depth":17},{"id":142,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"Trump ' s address was peppered with several lines","depth":16},{"id":144,"text":"that delighted the crowd in the Rose Garden ,","depth":16},{"id":145,"text":"along with sky-high estimates of the economic toll","depth":17},{"id":146,"text":"he said","depth":17},{"id":147,"text":"the U.S. would suffer","depth":17},{"id":148,"text":"if it remained in the deal .","depth":17},{"id":149,"text":"Those figures ,","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"including a prediction","depth":17},{"id":151,"text":"that U.S. gross domestic product would fall $ 2.9 trillion by 2040 ,","depth":17},{"id":152,"text":"were taken from a March study by NERA Economic Consulting","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"that didn ' t consider any economic benefits","depth":17},{"id":154,"text":"the country might gain from cleaner air , new jobs or reduced impacts from global warming .","depth":17},{"id":155,"text":"In fact , Americans in 2015 spent the smallest share of their income on energy","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"since the federal Energy Information Administration started tracking the number in 1992 ,","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"even as energy-related greenhouse gas emissions have fallen since 2005 .","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"Trump said","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"he would also halt Obama 's promised payment of `` tens of billions of dollars '' to the Green Climate Fund , an international program","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"aimed at helping poor countries cope with climate change .","depth":15},{"id":161,"text":"Obama actually pledged $ 3 billion ,","depth":16},{"id":162,"text":"and the U.S. contributed $ 1 billion to the fund","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"before he left office .","depth":15},{"id":164,"text":"Trump argued","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"that the Paris deal `` punishes the United States , ''","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"calling it a `` massive redistribution of United States wealth to other countries . ''","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"Absent from the ceremony were three of the administration 's biggest advocates","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"for remaining in the deal :","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"Ivanka Trump , her husband , Jared Kushner , and Secretary of State Rex Tillerson .","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"National Economic Council Director Gary Cohn , another aide","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"who favored staying ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"sat in the front row .","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"Several Cabinet members also attended ,","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"including E nvironmental Protection Agency Administrator Scott Pruitt , Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin .","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"In a briefing after the speech , senior administration officials would not say","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"whether Trump believes","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"that human activity contributes to climate change .","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"The president ' s remarks speak for themselves ,","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"one official said ,","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"and called the question on his beliefs off-topic .","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"Trump is \" sincere \" about re-opening negotiations for a new or altered climate deal","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"and is \" very intent \" in engaging in such negotiations ,","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"the aides said .","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"But foreign governments were quick to reject the idea","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"that the Paris agreement ,","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"in which numerous countries made concessions","depth":17},{"id":187,"text":"to satisfy the domestic political considerations of the United States ,","depth":17},{"id":188,"text":"is up for renegotiating .","depth":15},{"id":189,"text":"\" We deem the momentum","depth":17},{"id":190,"text":"generated in Paris in December 2015","depth":17},{"id":191,"text":"irreversible","depth":16},{"id":192,"text":"and we firmly believe","depth":16},{"id":193,"text":"that the Paris Agreement can not be renegotiated ,","depth":17},{"id":194,"text":"since it is a vital instrument for our planet , societies and economies , \"","depth":17},{"id":195,"text":"the governments of France , Germany and Italy said in a joint statement .","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"In a similar statement , the U nited N ations said","depth":15},{"id":197,"text":"that","depth":16},{"id":198,"text":"while it \" stands ready to engage in dialogue with the United States government ,","depth":17},{"id":199,"text":"\" the Paris deal \" can not be renegotiated","depth":18},{"id":200,"text":"based on the request of a single Party . \"","depth":18},{"id":201,"text":"`` This is a Trumpian ruse , ''","depth":16},{"id":202,"text":"one European official told .","depth":16},{"id":203,"text":"`` Paris , in effect , took 20 years to negotiate","depth":16},{"id":204,"text":"and reflects a profound accommodation of U.S. demands for flexibility . ''","depth":16},{"id":205,"text":"Asked about the dim reaction from Europe ,","depth":15},{"id":206,"text":"one administration official paused .","depth":15},{"id":207,"text":"`` There ' s no question","depth":17},{"id":208,"text":"that other countries are going to want to sit down with us","depth":18},{"id":209,"text":"and discuss the potential way forward , \"","depth":18},{"id":210,"text":"the official continued ,","depth":16},{"id":211,"text":"before adding :","depth":16},{"id":212,"text":"\" I don ' t know","depth":17},{"id":213,"text":"what that 's going to look like . ''","depth":17},{"id":214,"text":"White House officials briefed conservative groups and congressional staff earlier Thursday about the details of the withdrawal ,","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"distributing talking points","depth":14},{"id":216,"text":"that bashed the deal .","depth":14},{"id":217,"text":"Officials said","depth":13},{"id":218,"text":"they will withdraw","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"using the underlying terms of the deal ,","depth":15},{"id":220,"text":"which means a formal exit probably could not occur until November 2020 .","depth":15},{"id":221,"text":"That date means that `` Paris will be on the ballot '' in 2020 ,","depth":16},{"id":222,"text":"Brian Deese , Obama 's former climate adviser , wrote on Twitter .","depth":16},{"id":223,"text":"Drama over Trump 's decision escalated in recent weeks","depth":12},{"id":224,"text":"as Pope Francis and numerous world leaders urged him to stay in the deal ,","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"and as the agreement drew widespread support from U.S. businesses","depth":14},{"id":226,"text":"- from Apple , IBM and Tesla to oil and gas giant ExxonMobil .","depth":14},{"id":227,"text":"One Trump adviser said","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"dozens of people had tried to persuade the president to take a more moderate approach ,","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"such as establishing a commission","depth":16},{"id":230,"text":"to study climate change","depth":16},{"id":231,"text":"or launching a 90-day review period .","depth":15},{"id":232,"text":"But Trump kept coming back to the economy ,","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"saying","depth":15},{"id":234,"text":"the accord would kill American jobs","depth":16},{"id":235,"text":"and `` these international agreements are not good for America , ''","depth":16},{"id":236,"text":"the person said .","depth":14},{"id":237,"text":"View","depth":3},{"id":238,"text":"Paris accord withdrawal is symbolic ,","depth":4},{"id":239,"text":"rollback of regulations is the real policy","depth":4},{"id":240,"text":"Nick Juliano reports on why the Paris accord withdrawal is largely symbolic , and in some cases , why it does n't really matter .","depth":4},{"id":241,"text":"It may anger those","depth":7},{"id":242,"text":"who favor climate change regulations ,","depth":7},{"id":243,"text":"but Trump has already begun the process","depth":7},{"id":244,"text":"to roll those back .","depth":7},{"id":245,"text":"`` You could n't talk him out of it , ''","depth":7},{"id":246,"text":"the person said .","depth":7},{"id":247,"text":"`` He thought","depth":8},{"id":248,"text":"it was a bad deal ,","depth":8},{"id":249,"text":"and he said over and over ,","depth":9},{"id":250,"text":"this is a bad deal .","depth":9},{"id":251,"text":"This hurts the economy .","depth":9},{"id":252,"text":"This is a bad deal . ''","depth":9},{"id":253,"text":"A slew of conservative activists attended the president 's speech ,","depth":6},{"id":254,"text":"including Myron Ebell , a former member of Trump 's presidential transition team and staffer at the Competitive Enterprise Institute","depth":8},{"id":255,"text":"who rejects mainstream climate science ,","depth":8},{"id":256,"text":"Heritage Foundation founder Ed Feulner and Americans for Tax Reform President Grover Norquist .","depth":7},{"id":257,"text":"A U.S. withdrawal will deal a severe blow to global cohesion on climate change at a time","depth":8},{"id":258,"text":"when","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"scientists say","depth":10},{"id":260,"text":"the world has few years left","depth":11},{"id":261,"text":"to head off the worst impacts of warming temperatures and rising seas .","depth":11},{"id":262,"text":"U.S. intelligence and military leaders have described climate change as a security problem ,","depth":9},{"id":263,"text":"warning","depth":10},{"id":264,"text":"it could cause mass migrations and inflame global conflicts .","depth":10},{"id":265,"text":"`` Eighty-three countries run into danger","depth":12},{"id":266,"text":"of disappearing from the surface of the Earth","depth":12},{"id":267,"text":"if we do n't resolutely start the fight against climate change , \"","depth":11},{"id":268,"text":"European Commission President Jean-Claude Juncker said Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":269,"text":"as word of Trump ' s expected decision began to leak .","depth":9},{"id":270,"text":"Supporters of the deal also see economic opportunities in the shift toward energy efficiency and green energy ,","depth":8},{"id":271,"text":"and accuse","depth":9},{"id":272,"text":"Trump and his team are squandering them .","depth":9},{"id":273,"text":"\" What ' s really stupid about it is they ' re throwing out the economic opportunities","depth":10},{"id":274,"text":"that being part of the Paris agreement provide for the United States , \"","depth":10},{"id":275,"text":"Hillary Clinton said Wednesday in an appearance at a tech industry conference .","depth":9},{"id":276,"text":"\" That is what I find totally incomprehensible . \"","depth":8},{"id":277,"text":"In the run-up to the Paris conference , Obama had pledged","depth":7},{"id":278,"text":"that the U.S. would reduce its greenhouse gas emissions to 26 percent to 28 percent below 2005 levels by 2025 ,","depth":8},{"id":279,"text":"largely by carrying out his policies","depth":9},{"id":280,"text":"of tightening regulations on power plants and vehicles","depth":10},{"id":281,"text":"while encouraging a shift toward greater reliance on wind and solar power .","depth":10},{"id":282,"text":"But the Obama administration had insisted","depth":7},{"id":283,"text":"those targets be non binding ,","depth":8},{"id":284,"text":"allowing the pact to avoid the Senate ratification requirement","depth":9},{"id":285,"text":"that doomed U.S. support for the 1997 Kyoto climate agreement .","depth":9},{"id":286,"text":"Regardless of the fate of the Paris agreement ,","depth":6},{"id":287,"text":"Trump has already moved to shelve the entirety of Obama ' s domestic climate agenda ,","depth":7},{"id":288,"text":"ensuring","depth":8},{"id":289,"text":"that the U.S. will most likely miss Obama ' s targets .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":579,"left":526,"right":578,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":526,"left":292,"right":525,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":291,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":291,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":525,"left":346,"right":524,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":346,"left":326,"right":345,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":326,"left":293,"right":325,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":293,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":325,"left":296,"right":324,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":294,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":315,"right":323,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":315,"left":301,"right":314,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":298,"right":300,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":9,"right":297,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":297,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":299,"right":14,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"l